description:
In this episode, we take a look into the life of Scottish protestant reformer, George Wishart. George lived just 33 years, yet he made a significant impact on Scotland through his Godly life and powerful preaching, before he was captured by Cardinal Beaton. He also mentored and trained the man who would solidify and carry forward the Scottish Reformation: John Knox.

To find out more information about George Wishart visit our website to read to our extended article.
